import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Miles_per_Gallon'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Miles_per_Gallon', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x='Displacement', y='Weight_in_lbs', data=data)
    ax.set_xlabel('Engine Displacement')
    ax.set_ylabel('Weight in lbs')
    ax.set_title('How does the weight of the cars vary with their engine displacement?', wrap=True)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Horsepower'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Horsepower'], errors='coerce')
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data['Horsepower'])
    ax.set(xlabel='Horsepower')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Horsepower?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['Horsepower'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Horsepower'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
